In this letter, President Barack Obama informs the Speaker of the House about the deployment of additional U.S. Armed Forces personnel to Iraq. The purpose of this deployment is to provide security and support for U.S. personnel and facilities, including the U.S. Embassy in Baghdad. The force is equipped for combat and will remain in Iraq until the security situation improves. The President states that this action is being undertaken in coordination with the Government of Iraq and is in line with his responsibility to protect U.S. citizens and further U.S. national security and foreign policy interests. The President is providing this report to Congress to fulfill his obligations under the War Powers Resolution.